# -----------------------
# UDP Publisher (GCS -> gateway UDP/9000)
# -----------------------
# The gateway container usually has TWO IPs:
#   1) Bridge IP: internal Docker "vision" network (host can reach this)
#   2) Macvlan IP: physical LAN IP (remote machines can reach this)
#
# Find BOTH IPs (prints one per attached Docker network, space-separated):
#   docker inspect -f '{{range .NetworkSettings.Networks}}{{.IPAddress}} {{end}}' vision_stack-gateway-1
#
# Rule:
# - If GCS runs on the SAME HOST (network_mode: host), use the BRIDGE IP.
# - If GCS runs REMOTELY (over ethernet/radio), use the MACVLAN (LAN) IP.
#
# Example output:
#   172.30.10.4 192.168.1.23
# Then set:
#   UDP_DST_IP=172.30.10.4   # local host-mode GCS
#   UDP_DST_IP=192.168.1.23  # remote GCS

#UDP_DST_IP=192.168.1.2

# Home
#UDP_DST_IP=172.19.0.3

# Work
#UDP_DST_IP=172.30.10.3
#UDP_DST_IP=gateway

UDP_DST_IP=192.168.1.50
UDP_DST_PORT=9000